# Definition of Done

A migration step is **done** when ALL of these are true:

## 1. Content is modeled
- [ ] Payload collection, global, or block exists with correct fields
- [ ] Fields that need localization have `localized: true`
- [ ] Media fields use `upload` type pointing to media collection
- [ ] Schema is derived from the **existing** content structure (not invented)

## 2. Content is seeded
- [ ] A seed script exists that populates this content
- [ ] The seed is deterministic (upsert pattern — safe to re-run)
- [ ] The seed imports data from the current hardcoded source when applicable
- [ ] Media assets are uploaded via seed (not manually)
- [ ] Running the seed → logging into admin → content is immediately visible

## 3. Frontend renders from Payload
- [ ] The relevant page/component fetches data from Payload Local API
- [ ] The page renders correctly with Payload data
- [ ] Visual quality matches or improves on the current version
- [ ] Mobile and desktop breakpoints work

## 4. Old hardcoded data is cleaned up
- [ ] Hardcoded data for this feature is removed (or marked for removal)
- [ ] No orphan imports or unused type definitions left behind
- [ ] If other pages still use shared data, only remove what's safe

## 5. Build passes
- [ ] `pnpm build` succeeds
- [ ] No TypeScript errors
- [ ] No lint errors (if lint is configured)

## 6. Branch safety
- [ ] Changes are on a feature branch (not `main` or `master`)
- [ ] Commit messages are clear and descriptive
- [ ] PR is ready for review

## Quick checklist format

```
## Done?
- [x] Schema exists
- [x] Seed works (idempotent)
- [x] Admin shows content
- [x] Frontend renders from Payload
- [x] Mobile + desktop checked
- [x] Old data removed
- [x] Build passes
- [x] On feature branch
```
